Nigerian Court Halts Governor Votes in 5 States, Vanguard Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-02-24T08:34:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/nigerian-court-halts-governor-votes-in-5-states-vanguard-says.html
  Nigeria ’s Federal High Court in the
capital, Abuja, ruled that the electoral commission should
cancel governorship votes in five states slated for April,
 Vanguard  reported, citing Justice Adamu Bello.  The governors of the central Kogi state, the southern
Bayelsa and Cross River states and the northern Sokoto and
Adamawa states have a year left in their four-year tenure after
winning re-run election in 2008, Bello said, according to the
Lagos-based newspaper.  Africa’s most populous country and top oil producer will
hold a presidential election on April 9. There will also be a
federal legislative vote on April 2 and state elections on April
16.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dulue Mbachu at 
 dmbachu@bloomberg.net . 